dismissalComment.html: its pulled high in the air towards long leg, Santner gets under the ball and takes the catch just before the rope. Sounded great coming off the bat, just died before going over the rope

commentTextItems.html: its over, its all over. Its a short ball and Mahmudullah pulls the ball to the mid-wicket boundary to win the game

commentPostTextItems.html: At the end of the day, Bangladesh made it home with 10 balls to spare. Recording their first ever ODI win over New Zealand outside of Bangladesh.
In a game of big 2nd wicket partnerships, Bangladesh has their own between Tamim and Sabbir.
Despite a mid-innings wobble, both Mushfiqur and Mahmudullah played beautifully to steady the ship and set the team on the road to victory.
Taking wickets was what slowed down the New Zealand innings, yet the their bowlers couldn't take the wickets to do the same to the Bangladeshi team.
With the win today Bangladesh climb ahead of Sri Lanka in the one day rankings. Too make today even more special for the fans that came to the ground today.
Mushfiqur Rahim has just been named Man of the Match.
Tom Latham has just been named man of the series.

New Zealand finish top of the pile with 12 points, beating Bangladesh by two points to claim the Tri-Series trophy. Hopefully this series will have whetted your appetite for the Champions Trophy to come.
That just leaves me to thank you for following my commentary over the past two weeks. Its been a pleasure to bring it to you. Till me meet again, this is Justin Smyth saying goodnight from Clontarf!

commentTextItems.html: cuts the ball out to the cover sweeper, Munro gets down to field
its pulled out to the deep square leg boundary, 5 runs needed

commentTextItems.html: Yorker from Henry, the batsman are swinging at everything and its an inside edge through square leg
get another short ball, Rahim gets on top of the ball and plays it down through square leg
expects the short ball and gets it. Angles the bat and lifts it down to third man
clips the ball into the legside, its past the close fielder and Bangladesh edge a run closer
wide of off-stump, cuts the ball into the ground and its stopped at backward point
gets up on his toes and plays the ball out to point. Loud shout of no from Rahim, don't need another run out at this stage.

commentTextItems.html: its a short ball and its pulled towards the square leg boundary. It keeps going and it lands just over the rope. The crowd erupts here..
slower ball outside off-stump and Rahim waits for the ball, guides it down to third man
full ball, driven up along the ground to Patel at long-off

commentPostTextItems.html: The batsmen have a quick chat in the middle....

commentTextItems.html: its in the slot and Mahmudullah look to pull the ball into the legside, goes over the top of Santner's head at mid-on and races away to the rope
its yet another short ball from Bennett, the batsman tries to pull the ball into the legside, gets nothing on it and it goes through to the keeper
Henry goes short and gthe ball is pulled into the legside, it lands safe and goes out to the fielder on the boundary

commentTextItems.html: good bouncer that time, Mahmudullah looks to pull the ball and misses.
skips down the pitch and the bowler sees him coming, drops short and the batsman can't get anything on the ball
gets onto the front foot and plays the ball into the off-side. No chance of a run there as the bowler runs down and fields
its pulled towards the backward square leg boundary, Bennett chases the ball and can't catch it up. That's 3000 ODI runs for Mahmudullah
gets a little tickle on the ball down the legside, goes to fine leg and Bennett fields
